CANCEL FORWARD
Put the dedicated service code for deactivating unconditionally forwarding call

NOTIFICATION STATUS
Enable persistent notification when duty schedule is triggered

ACTIVATE FORWARD
Put in the field below, the dedicated service code for activating unconditionally forward for all calls
Example: *21*+33687272643#
Label: Code for checking forward service status

CHECK STATUS
Put the dedicated service code for checking unconditionally forward status

DutyManager is a simple application for people which manage on call duty. It is based on your pre-defined list configured into the app and set up unconditional call forward for you. This task is automatically triggered by a keyword separated by a space found in the description of any calendar hosted in the phone. Any keyword can be used (name, surname, trigram, etc ...)

Here you can find a scrolling list of your duty contact. First field is your event keyword which trigger the call forwarding task. It has to match the first same keyword in your calendar description event.

To add an entry: Tap on + button
To delete an entry: Long tap on the trash icon

REBOOT FUNCTION
Put in the field below, the dedicated keyword in order to restart your device remotely
Note: it is more secure to use a kind of password combinaison with your keyword

REMOTE FUNCTION - OVERRIDE
Short code to override current shift by the provided phone number
Example: TAKEOVER:+33687272643

REMOTE FUNCTION - STATUS
Query the current status set on the phone

REMOTE FUNCTION - ADD CONTACT
Short code to remotely add a new contact
Example : ADD#John:+33723456788

TEXT MESSAGE
Send a text message each time duty schedule starts
